### Configure Transformers.js Environment Settings

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Explains how to configure the Transformers.js environment using the `env` object. This includes settings for model loading (disabling remote models, setting custom paths, enabling local file URLs), ONNX Runtime (WASM paths, thread count, proxy), and device selection (checking WebGPU support). It also demonstrates setting up progress callbacks during pipeline creation.

```javascript
import { env, pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// --- Model Loading Configuration ---

// Use local models only (disable Hugging Face Hub)
env.allowRemoteModels = false;

// Set custom local model path
env.localModelPath = '/path/to/models/';

// Set custom cache directory (Node.js)
env.cacheDir = './.cache';

// Allow loading from local file:// URLs
env.allowLocalModels = true;

// --- ONNX Runtime Configuration ---

// Set custom WASM file locations
env.backends.onnx.wasm.wasmPaths = '/path/to/wasm/files/';

// Use specific WASM backend
env.backends.onnx.wasm.numThreads = 4;

// Proxy configuration for WASM files
env.backends.onnx.wasm.proxy = true;

// --- Progress Callbacks ---

// Track model download progress
const pipe = await pipeline('sentiment-analysis', 'Xenova/bert-base-uncased', {
    progress_callback: (progress) => {
        if (progress.status === 'downloading') {
            console.log(`Downloading: ${progress.file} - ${progress.progress}%`);
        } else if (progress.status === 'done') {
            console.log(`Downloaded: ${progress.file}`);
        }
    }
});

// --- Device Selection ---

// Check WebGPU support
console.log('WebGPU supported:', await env.backends.onnx.webgpu.isSupported());

// --- Example: Complete Configuration ---

// Configure before loading models
env.allowRemoteModels = true;
env.localModelPath = './models/';
env.backends.onnx.wasm.numThreads = 4;

const classifier = await pipeline('sentiment-analysis', null, {
    progress_callback: (data) => {
        console.log(data);
    }
});
```

