### Transformers.js Pipeline API - Model Loading Options

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Illustrates advanced model loading options using `PretrainedOptions`. This includes specifying data type (quantization/precision), selecting a compute device (e.g., WebGPU), loading a specific model revision, and configuring local model usage.

```javascript
import { pipeline, env } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Load full-precision model (fp32) instead of default quantized version
const pipe1 = await pipeline('feature-extraction', 'Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2', {
    dtype: 'fp32'  // Options: 'fp32', 'fp16', 'q8', 'q4', 'q4f16'
});

// Use WebGPU for GPU acceleration
const pipe2 = await pipeline('text-generation', 'onnx-community/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct', {
    dtype: 'q4',
    device: 'webgpu'
});

// Load specific model revision (branch/commit)
