### Handle Translation and Model Loading in Web Worker (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/react.md

This JavaScript code for a Web Worker listens for messages from the main thread. It initializes a translation pipeline, handles model loading progress via callbacks, performs translation using a streamer for partial output, and sends completion or update messages back to the main thread.

```javascript
// Listen for messages from the main thread
self.addEventListener('message', async (event) => {
  // Retrieve the translation pipeline. When called for the first time,
  // this will load the pipeline and save it for future use.
  const translator = await MyTranslationPipeline.getInstance(x => {
      // We also add a progress callback to the pipeline so that we can
      // track model loading.
      self.postMessage(x);
  });

  // Capture partial output as it streams from the pipeline
  const streamer = new TextStreamer(translator.tokenizer, {
      skip_prompt: true,
      skip_special_tokens: true,
      callback_function: function (text) {
          self.postMessage({
              status: 'update',
              output: text
          });
      }
  });

  // Actually perform the translation
  const output = await translator(event.data.text, {
      tgt_lang: event.data.tgt_lang,
      src_lang: event.data.src_lang,

      // Allows for partial output to be captured
      streamer,
  });

  // Send the output back to the main thread
  self.postMessage({
      status: 'complete',
      output,
  });
});
```

